                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1583183463002-what-about-co-op-and-internships-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#3c7b627f-8dc7-429f-acb4-71c6c24917f6" href="#accordion-content-1583183463002-what-about-co-op-and-internships-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1583183463002-what-about-co-op-and-internships-" aria-expanded="false">
                            What about co-op and internships?
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1583183463002-what-about-co-op-and-internships-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1583183463002-what-about-co-op-and-internships-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1583183463002 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="2566af8a-4bd7-4690-b6a8-658d62558099" >

    <p>Some programs of study at Ryerson include work or internships as a part of the curriculum.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>Regardless of whether the program is a co-op program (e.g. Chemical Engineering) or an internship opportunity (e.g. Nursing), <strong>international students are required to apply for the Co-op Work Permit to participate in these employment opportunities.&nbsp;</strong></p> 
<p>Students must be in possession of the Co-op Work Permit <strong>BEFORE</strong> the work term or placement opportunity begins. From an immigration perspective, it does not matter whether or not the student is being paid for the work. </p>
    





</div>
